.TH "cs4270_set_dai_fmt" 9 "cs4270_set_dai_fmt" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
cs4270_set_dai_fmt \- configure the codec for the selected audio format
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" cs4270_set_dai_fmt
.BI "(struct snd_soc_dai *codec_dai "  ","
.BI "unsigned int format "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "codec_dai" 12
the codec DAI
.IP "format" 12
a SND_SOC_DAIFMT_x value indicating the data format
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function takes a bitmask of SND_SOC_DAIFMT_x bits and programs the
codec accordingly.

Currently, this function only supports SND_SOC_DAIFMT_I2S and
SND_SOC_DAIFMT_LEFT_J.  The CS4270 codec also supports right-justified
data for playback only, but ASoC currently does not support different
formats for playback vs. record.
